Multi-Cluster

Show workload placement like multi-cluster (even with 1 cluster)


CLI Step 1: Label nodes
oc get nodes
oc label node <worker-node> env=cluster1
CLI Step 2: Create app with placement
oc new-project student-n1
oc create deployment loan-app --image=nginx
oc patch deployment loan-app -p '{
"spec": {
  "template": {
    "spec": {
      "nodeSelector": {
        "env": "cluster1"
      }
    }
  }
}}'

Verify (CLI)
oc get pods -o wide

Pod should land on that node

