Security recommandation

1. Identity & Access Management (IAM)
Recommendations
Enforce SSO integration (LDAP / Azure AD / IAM Identity Center)
Use RBAC with least privilege
Avoid giving cluster-admin to users
Use groups instead of individual users
Example
oc adm policy add-role-to-user admin student1 -n student-n1

Separate roles:
Dev → namespace access
Ops → cluster access
Security → read-only audit


2. Network Security
Recommendations
Apply default deny network policies
Allow only required traffic (micro-segmentation)
Use namespace isolation
Example (deny all)
kind: NetworkPolicy
spec:
  podSelector: {}
  policyTypes:
  - Ingress


3. Container & Image Security
Recommendations
Use trusted/private registries
Enable image scanning
Avoid latest tag
Use minimal base images (alpine, distroless)
Example
image: nginx:1.25


4. Pod Security (Runtime Security)
Recommendations
Run containers as non-root
Drop unnecessary Linux capabilities
Use read-only root filesystem
Example
securityContext:
  runAsNonRoot: true


5. Data & Storage Security
Recommendations
Encrypt data at rest
Encrypt traffic in transit (TLS)
Restrict PVC access
Avoid shared volumes unless required


6. Secrets Management
Recommendations
Never store secrets in plain YAML
Use:
Kubernetes Secrets
External vaults (HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager)
Example
oc create secret generic db-secret --from-literal=password=admin123




